\id MAT eng-test
\h Matthew
\c 4
\p
\v 23 And Jesus went about all Galilee, \add teaching\add* in their synagogues.
\v 24 And his fame went throughout all Syria.\f + \fr 4:24 \ft A footnote to strip.\f*
\v 25 And there followed him great multitudes of people.
\c 5
\s1 The Beatitudes
\p
\v 1 And seeing the multitudes, he went up into a mountain:
and when he was set, his disciples came unto him.
\v 2 And he opened his mouth, and taught them, saying,
\q1
\v 3 Blessed \w are\w* the poor in spirit: for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
\s1 Salt and Light
\q1
\v 13 Ye are the salt of the earth.\x + \xo 5:13 \xt Mark 9:50\x*
